text: Arizona's 27th Legislative District is one of 30 in the state, situated in south central Maricopa County. As of 2018 there are 37 precincts in the district, with a total registered voter population of 92,595. ==Political representation== The district is represented for the 2019-2021 Legislative Session in the State Senate by Rebecca Rios (D, Phoenix) and in the House of Representatives by Reginald Bolding (D, Phoenix) and Diego Rodriguez (D, Phoenix). ==References== Category:Maricopa County, Arizona Category:Arizona legislative districts
title: Arizona's 27th legislative district
